<br>
The Mana Preservation effect impacts both effective mana pool and effective mana regneration rate. It could be replaced by an effect which scaled with mana pool (making it bigger) and mana regen (making it faster).<br>
<br>
The conversion effect formulas follow (note: fractions are preserved):<br>
<br>
Effective Pool Boost = Pool * (1 / (1 - Conservation %) - 1)<br>
<br>
Effective Regen Boost = Regen * (1 / (1 - Conservation %) - 1)<br>
<br>
So, a wizard with 2700 mana and an average regen of 27 mana/tick would have to replace a 10% conservation 3 item  with one which provided at least 300 mana and FT3 to gain the same benefit.<br>
<br>
However, a wizard with 1800 mana and average regen of 18 mana/tick would have to replace a 10% conservation 3 item with one which provided at least 200 mana and FT2 to gain the same benefit.<br>
<br>
BTW: sitting (meditating) regen for an unbuffed wizard at level 60 is 20 mana/tick. This has been verified by myself and several others on this board by taking careful measurements. <p>"Evacuate? In our moment of triumph? I think you overestimate their chances!"<BR>
